{{Infobox ancient site|type = {{ill|zenpō-kōhō-fun|lt=zenpō-kōhō-fun|ja|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}}| name=Ōzuka Kofun| location={{ill|Toyama, Toyama|ja|富山市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyama, Toyama|qq=}}, Fuchū-machi Hane 3-1| position=| type=Rectangular keyhole-shaped mound| map_size=Total length approximately 58m; rear section height 7.6m| Interred_individual=Unknown| built=Early Kofun built| burial goods=| historic_site_Historic Site=January 15, 1948 (National Historic Site)| image=}}
'''Ōzuka Kofun''' (王塚古墳) is a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun|qq=}} located in {{ill|Toyama City|ja|富山市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyama City|qq=}}, {{ill|Toyama Prefecture|ja|富山県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyama Prefecture|qq=}}. It is a {{ill|Zenpō-kōhō-fun|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun (keyhole-shaped mound)|ja|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpō-kōhō-fun|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}}, built during the early {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun period|qq=}}. The tumulus was Historic Site1 a National Historic Site on January 15, 1948.
== Overview == The Ōzuka Kofun is situated on a ridge of the Hane Hills at an altitude of 130 meters<ref name="ze" />, covering a historic site area of 2,452 square meters<ref name="men" />. It is a large keyhole-shaped mound measuring 58 meters in total length with the rear mound standing 7.6 meters high. It Ranks as the fourth-largest kofun in Toyama Prefecture<ref name="men">[https://www.city.toyama.toyama.jp/etc/maibun/center/topics/ohduka_senbouyama/ohduka_senbouyama.htm Ōzuka and Senbōyama Ruins] (Toyama City, accessed October 8, 2023).</ref>. The tumulus overlooks the Toyama Plain to the east<ref name="ze">[https://www.toyamashi-kankoukyoukai.jp/?tid=101831 Ōzuka Kofun] (Toyama City Tourism Official Website TOYAMANET, accessed October 8, 2023).</ref>.
* Total length: 58 m<ref name="a">[https://toyama-bunkaisan.jp/search/1628/ Ōzuka and Senbōyama Ruins] (Toyama Historic Site, accessed October 8, 2023).</ref> * Maximum width: 26 m<ref name="a" /> * Height: 4 m<ref name="a" /> * Rear mound width: 33 m<ref name="a" /> * Rear mound height: 7.6 m<ref name="a" />
The tumulus was Historic Site1 a National Historic Site on January 15, 1948, and in 2004, the surrounding Kofuns and graves were also Historic Site1 as National Historic Sites<ref>''Toyama City History: Chronological History (Volume II)'' (published March 20, 2015, Toyama City), p. 683.</ref>.
== Surroundings == The area includes other representative kofun and settlements from the late {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yayoi period|qq=}} to the early Kofun period, such as the Chokushizuka Kofun and Senbōyama Ruins<ref name="ze" />.
== Access == * From {{ill|Toyama Station|ja|富山駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyama Station|qq=}}, take the {{ill|JR West Takayama Main Line|ja|高山本線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR West Takayama Main Line|qq=}} for 15 minutes to {{ill|Hayahoshi Station|ja|速星駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayahoshi Station|qq=}}, then a 10-minute taxi ride<ref name="ze" />. * From {{ill|Toyama Nishi IC|ja|富山西インターチェンジ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyama Nishi IC|qq=}} on the {{ill|Hokuriku Expressway|ja|北陸自動車道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokuriku Expressway|qq=}}, a 10-minute drive (free parking available for 120 cars)<ref name="ze" />. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kofun in Japan|ja|日本の古墳一覧|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Kofun in Japan|qq=}} * * {{ill|List of Historic Sites in the Chūbu region|ja|中部地方の史跡一覧|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Historic Sites in the Chūbu region|qq=}}
